I hope this is an appropriate group to pose my question.  Anyway, here goes:

For the sake of discussion call my site MYDOMAIN.COM and call the other
site OTHER.COM.  I am connected to OTHER.COM via uucp.  OTHER.COM is not
connected to the internet, but I am willing to act as a mail exchanger on
the internet for OTHER.COM.  I have added the following MX record to my
nameserver:

	OTHER.COM.   IN   MX  10   MAILHOST.MYDOMAIN.COM.

What happens is that everyone in MYDOMAIN.COM knows that MAILHOST is
acting as the mail exchanger for OTHER.COM, but no one else on the
internet knows that I am OTHER.COM's mail exchanger.  I suppose
since OTHER.COM is outside my zone of authority that NIC needs to
be told of this arrangement.  Does anyone know what needs to be
done?

-- 
Internet: markb@slc.unisys.com			uucp: ...!giga!markb
	  markb@signus.utah.edu

